ActCustoms Tariff
SubjectCIFTA Rules of Origin Regulations
PrecisCIFTA RULES OF ORIGIN REGULATIONS in order to repeal and replace the Canada-Israel Free Trade Agreement (CIFTA) Rules of Origin Regulations (SOR/97-63) and implement, in Canada, the rules of origin negotiated by Canada and Israel in the modernized CIFTA that will be used to determine when goods have undergone sufficient production to qualify for preferential tariff treatment.
